Cyprian Shakiwawa - Lawyer, member of the Training Core of the Umoja Associated organization ESCAA in Tanzania said; “In Tanzania, the courts rely a lot on the findings of a family officer, so it is important that the officers themselves undergo mandatory structured training. Huzaifa Katulani - Lawyer also a member of TCCN project said; Clients often bring many questions to the court that are not on the jurisdiction of the court, so when it comes to civil law, they ask the court to issue an order to do family counseling to refer them to the marriage officer, even though it is not the job of the court to do the same. There is no mechanism or procedure to refer the potential future spouse of missing spouse to the family officer who was married with the complainant. This procedure contributes to delay in the divorce process.
